tv.amwa.maj.record

Interface TimecodeValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<TimecodeValue>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TimecodeValueImpl

    public interface TimecodeValue
extends Comparable<TimecodeValue>

    Specifies videotape or audio tape timecode information. The timecode interface is capable of representing timecode values specified by SMPTE 12M.

    To make values of this type, use the following methods from the MAJ forge:

    • From its underlying component parts of frame count, frames per second and drop frame flag: Forge.makeTimecode(long, short, boolean);
    • Calculated from the SMPTE 12M component values: Forge.calculateTimecode(short, short, short, short, short, boolean);
    • Duration calculated from SOM and EOM timecodes: Forge.calculateDuration(TimecodeValue, TimecodeValue);>
    • End timecode calculated from SOM and duration: Forge.calculateEndTimecode(TimecodeValue, TimecodeValue);
    • From a string representation as generated by toString(): Forge.parseTimecode(String).
    See Also:
    TimecodeSegment

    • Method Detail

      • getDropFrame

        boolean getDropFrame()

        Determines whether the timecode is drop (true value) or nondrop (false value).

        If drop is set to true, the real frames-per-second rate represented by the timecode is 29.97. Calculations of the real time represented by a timecode or to create a textual representation of the time code drop 108 selected frames per hour.

        Returns:
        Is the timecode a drop value?

      • convertToRealTime

        TimeStruct convertToRealTime()
                      throws NumberFormatException

        Converts the timecode value to a real time, taking account of the frames per second and drop frame values. The value returned is a TimeStruct value, containing the hours, minutes, seconds and fractions of a second represented by the frame offset value returned by getStartTimecode().

        Returns:
        A time value representing the real time offset of the timecode value.
        Throws:
        NumberFormatException - The timecode value is larger than the range it is possible to represent with a time structure value.

      • toString

        String toString()

        Formats a timecode value representation in accordance with the SMPTE and EBU specifications. Specifically:

        • EBU TS N12-1999: "Time-and-control codes for television recording". 1999.
        • SMPTE 0012-2008: "SMPTE standard for television, audio and film - time and control code". February 2008. (Character format from SMPTE 0258-2004).

        The format of the returned value is "hh:mm:ss;ff(.p)?" for timecodes with drop frames and "hh:mm:ss:ff(.p)?" for timecodes with no drop frame. The components of the value of the timecode are:

        • hh is the number of hours
        • mm is the number of minutes;
        • ss is the number of seconds;
        • ff is the number of frames through this second;
          • .
        • (.p)? for frame rates over 30, whether the frame is the first (.0) or second (.1) of the pair.
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:
        String representation of this timecode value.
        See Also:
        Forge.parseTimecode(String)
